  <header>
    <h1>ARM-Based Network Monitoring Application</h1>
    <p>
      Transform your Raspberry Pi into a fully functional Network Operations Center (NOC).  
      Real-time service visibility, traffic analytics, and interface control ‚Äî optimized for ARM architectures.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>‚öôÔ∏è Comprehensive Port & Service Management</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><b>Ports & Protocols:</b> Monitors TCP and UDP services (SSH:22, DNS:53, HTTP:80, HTTPS:443).</li>
      <li><b>Process & PID Tracking:</b> Maps open ports to their exact processes (e.g., <code>dev-server</code>, PID 5678).</li>
      <li><b>Interface Binding:</b> Shows which network interface each service listens on (e.g., <code>0.0.0.0</code> or <code>127.0.0.1</code>).</li>
      <li><b>Centralized Control:</b> Includes action tools for managing, blocking, or restarting services directly from the UI.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>üåê Visual Traffic Flow Analysis</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><b>Traffic Segmentation:</b> Categorizes flows by region or type (Social-America, North America, Africa).</li>
      <li><b>Service-Level Routing:</b> Visualizes connections from the IPT Traffic Hub to specific ports (e.g., <code>rope:600</code>, <code>custom-app:8080</code>).</li>
      <li><b>Proportional Representation:</b> Line thickness reflects traffic volume and activity levels.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>üçì Optimized for Raspberry Pi & ARM</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><b>Low-Power Operation:</b> Runs 24/7 with minimal energy consumption.</li>
      <li><b>Cost-Effective:</b> Built for accessible ARM hardware like the Raspberry Pi.</li>
      <li><b>Compact & Portable:</b> Lightweight, deployable anywhere on the network.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

